title: For Sale/Trade:  Scammer Warning
postcontent:
There's a guy contacting those with postings and he seems pretty shady.  This is just a friendly reminder to be wary of those you give personal information to (full name, address, etc.) when acknowledging you have firearms at your residence.  

Here's the first email I got from "Richard Bolibger" that seems like a scam waiting to happen:  

Hello,
i need to know if this item is still available and Kindly get back to me with the asking price soon as possible so to proceed.

Note the poor English, the fact that he doesn't know the item or the price of what he's inquiring about - even though both are in the posting.  

Here's his second email:  


Hello,




   Thanks for your reply Concerning my inquiry.. $850 is a good price for this item...I am quite comfortable with the condition and price of the item but due to the nature of my health, I can not make or receive phone call as I am Impaired. I am also willing to pay for the shipment .. 




I want you to hold it for me before any other interested person mail you. Please provide your full name, Address and your Phone number so that I can send your payment. I will be paying you by Certified check. It will take 2 -3 days for the payment to get to you with a Tracking #...As for delivery, I will make arrangements for the pick-up after you have received payment, If this meets your approval, kindly get back to me, as soon as possible, with your name, phone # and mailing address where payment will be sent, so that I can make an arrangement on the Check.

Full Name:

Address:

city:

State:

Zipcode:

Phone #:

Note: As soon as you have your money in hand, we can talk about the picking up of the item. I would like you to take the posting off Arm list today cos am interested in it and want to make the payment now.

I am willing to provide a FFL address to ship to so that you will be sure I am not going to possess it illegally.

Best Regards

Richard.

Again, the poor English; the classis second line of inquiry asking for more details about me so he can establish a false relationship without giving up anything about himself; he may not even care about the rifle - he wants me to switch some funds for him / provide personal information for more direct follow-up scams / or some variation of these.  

His email address is:   REDACTED

Good luck and safe bidding.

title: Want To Buy:  Sellers Beware.........
postcontent:
......Shady characters lurk in the pages of online firearms listings. Protect yourselves. Always ask for current Washington State issued ID or DL and Washington State CPL or a WAC membership. Do this prior to the meet(never meet at your home). If they won't send you this information electronically, chances are they're not supposed to own a firearm. I am not a dealer, just a person who tried to sell a pistol. Met a potential buyer at a Walmart parking lot. He wouldn't share his ID and didn't have a CPL or WAC card. Scary moment, he got angry about the drive when I wouldn't get the pistol out for him to view. Fortunately, it was the busiest time of the day, got in my car and left. Long story short, get the info, make sure it's legit or just use a FFL. Be Safe.

plaintruth777 says "This posting is insane!  If you want to go beyond the law, that's YOUR problem......". Shouldn't that be prerogative? I wouldn't sell him a firearm.
